ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Music and Psychoanalysis is an engrossing exploration of the relationship between these two fields, with content organized around Freud and Lacan and some of their contemporary musics, as well as recent music scholarship that applies psychoanalysis in various ways. I would recommend the course for the opportunity to work with Professor Brodsky and to learn about psychoanalysis not only in its relationship to music, but also on its own account.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Most of the content of this course probably will not have a direct bearing on my research, but it was certainly helpful in suggesting how I might do innovative research. The course also demonstrated the importance of psychoanalysis to twentieth-century thought, allowing me to draw connections with topics I have studied in other courses.
